      "date": "2015-08-07 08:44:39.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n>This seems like a bug in the upstream kernel and not in Lustre. Have you submitted this patch upstream to get some review of this change?\nAndreas, yes, the problems is because part of kernel can't be compiled with -o0 (without optimization). But I believe kernel is always used to be compiled with optimization. So probably only Lustre need this part of code to be compiled without optimization. This is the reason I added this to Lustre code source but not send upstream.",
