        "subject": "LU-6931 kernel: fix kernel to be compiled with o0",
        "message": "LU-6931 kernel: fix kernel to be compiled with o0\n\nGcov requires code to be compiled without optimization (o0).\nLustre get some parts of kernel's code to compile ldiskfs.\nThere is kernel function that is used by Lustre and can't be\ncompiled without optimization.\n\nThis patch fix change operand type, so this function\ncan be compiled without optimization.\n\nSigned-off-by: Artem Blagodarenko <artem_blagodarenko@xyratex.com>\nChange-Id: I0aa9d8497a9646d2be41efe8e0329f491f9532d5\n"
